</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126501D814FF9B3CB4FADA333AFED6" pageId="65" pageNumber="1024" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD814FF9B3CB4FADA333AFED6" blockId="65.[151,1058,1376,1456]" pageId="65" pageNumber="1024">
E t y m o l o g y: 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D814FF9B3D46FADA3390FE13" box="[357,431,1376,1397]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="1024">Alarius</emphasis>
is a Latin name with a meaning of &quot;of wings&quot;; with reference to the lack of metathoracic wings in the 
<typeStatus id="54B38828D814FF9B3E7DFAC730B5FEF4" box="[606,650,1405,1426]" pageId="65" pageNumber="1024">type</typeStatus>
species of this genus. The gender is masculine.
</paragraph>
